Headlines: 36 Hours in Aarhus, Denmark
Snippets: This small and scholarly college town is brimming with discoveries, from astounding artwork to cozy restaurants and excellent craft beer.

Headlines: Crown Prince of Denmark Turned Away From Australian Bar for Lack of ID
Snippets: The episode has drawn attention to a new state law that has angered bar owners and patrons by requiring that identification cards be scanned to gain entry.

Headlines: Hamlet and the Surveillance State of Denmark
Snippets: Andrew Scott’s portrayal in a London production of “Hamlet” almost banishes other performances from memory.

Headlines: In Denmark, Lego House Is the New Kid on the Block
Snippets: The latest Lego attraction in Billund, the company’s headquarters, offers a collection of creative zones for children and grown-ups — as well as the world’s first Lego restaurant.

Headlines: Denmark’s Prince Henrik Wanted to Be King. So He’ll Protest for Eternity.
Snippets: Unhappy with the title of prince consort, which he considers a mark of gender inequality, the Danish royal says he doesn’t want to be buried beside his wife, the queen.

Headlines: Something Is Unspoken in the State of Denmark
Snippets: Free speech advocacy has become a cover for anti-Muslim nationalism.

Headlines: Birth Control Pills Still Linked to Breast Cancer, Study Finds
Snippets: Women using birth control pills and I.U.D.s that release hormones face a higher risk than those using methods without hormones, scientists in Denmark reported.

Headlines: In Denmark, Passage of Rules on Immigration Called for Cake
Snippets: Inger Stolberg, the country’s integration minister, celebrated the 50th regulation against immigration, spurring a public outcry — and praise.

Headlines: Denmark Says ‘Key Elements’ of Russian Government Hacked Defense Ministry
Snippets: The Kremlin denied the allegations that Russian hackers breached email accounts at Denmark’s Defense Ministry and Foreign Ministry in 2015 and 2016.

Headlines: Old, Ill and Ordered Deported From Denmark to Afghanistan
Snippets: A woman with dementia has been ordered to leave her family and return to her native country, reflecting Europe’s growing anti-immigrant sentiment.
